@title Clock auction for non-fungible tokens.
 @notice We omit a fallback function to prevent accidental sends to this contract.

@dev Remove all Ether from the contract, which is the owner's cuts
  as well as any Ether sent directly to the contract address.
  Always transfers to the NFT contract, but can be called either by
  the owner or the NFT contract.

@dev Returns the current price of an auction.
 @param _tokenId - ID of the token price we are checking.

bid(uint256).details: Bids on an open auction, completing the auction and transferring  ownership of the NFT if enough Ether is supplied.

params._tokenId: - ID of token to bid on.

cancelAuction(uint256).details: Cancels an auction that hasn't been won yet.  Returns the NFT to original owner.

cancelAuctionWhenPaused(uint256).details: Cancels an auction when the contract is paused.  Only the owner may do this, and NFTs are returned to  the seller. This should only be used in emergencies.

params._tokenId: - ID of the NFT on auction to cancel.

constructor.details: Constructor creates a reference to the NFT ownership contract  and verifies the owner cut is in the valid range.

params._cut: - percent cut the owner takes on each auction, must be  between 0-10,000.
params._nftAddress: - address of a deployed contract implementing  the Nonfungible Interface.

createAuction(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.details: Creates and begins a new auction.

params._duration: - Length of time to move between starting  price and ending price (in seconds).
params._endingPrice: - Price of item (in wei) at end of auction.
params._seller: - Seller, if not the message sender
params._startingPrice: - Price of item (in wei) at beginning of auction.
params._tokenId: - ID of token to auction, sender must be owner.

getAuction(uint256).details: Returns auction info for an NFT on auction.

getCurrentPrice(uint256).details: Returns the current price of an auction.

params._tokenId: - ID of the token price we are checking.

pause().details: called by the owner to pause, triggers stopped state

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

unpause().details: called by the owner to unpause, returns to normal state

withdrawBalance().details: Remove all Ether from the contract, which is the owner's cuts  as well as any Ether sent directly to the contract address.  Always transfers to the NFT contract, but can be called either by  the owner or the NFT contract.

InterfaceSignature_ERC721.details: The ERC-165 interface signature for ERC-721.  Ref: https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/165  Ref: https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/721

cancelAuction(uint256).notice: This is a state-modifying function that can  be called while the contract is paused.
